The paper titled \"Genomic Language Models\" by the authors at Stanford University (link: https://arxiv.org/abs/2205.01134) proposes a novel approach to modeling genomic sequences using language models. The model is trained on large-scale genomic data and can be fine-tuned for specific tasks such as variant calling, gene expression prediction, and genome assembly. The paper also discusses the use-cases of Genomic Language Models in various applications, including variant calling, gene expression prediction, and genome assembly.